<org.eclipse.epf.uma:ArtifactDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmi:id="-IhObwo9R3zdMYgLQkp4Gqg" name="method_arch,_aZI2ECy3Ed2TPpbydIQMow" guid="-IhObwo9R3zdMYgLQkp4Gqg" changeDate="2010-09-03T09:10:57.777-0700" version="7.5.0">
  <purpose>Analyze major architectural concerns and document architectural decisions. Assess and communicate the method architecture&#xD;
to stakeholders to ensure the&amp;nbsp;architecture will support the method needs of the organization.</purpose>
  <briefOutline>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The following are key pieces of information that should be described in this artifact:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Architecturally-significant decisions and rationale that drive content and organization of the elements in the&#xD;
        library: &#xD;
        &lt;ul>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Plug-in types, what they should contain and their allowable dependencies&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Configuration types and what should they contain&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Naming conventions&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Approach for defining navigation views&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Approach for categorizing elements&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Approach for assigning roles&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Approach for scaling elements&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Approach for associating guidance&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;/ul>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Architecturally-significant structural elements of the library and their relationships:&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li style=&quot;LIST-STYLE-TYPE: none&quot;>&#xD;
        &lt;ul>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Core method elements (for example: common standard categories, custom categories, roles, work products, and&#xD;
                tool mentors)&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Practices and their dependencies&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Practice configurations&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Architectural partitions, layers and their dependencies&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Key method elements (for example: roles, tasks, work products. guidance, and processes)&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;/ul>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></briefOutline>
  <representationOptions>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The format of the artifact is not as critical as the content.&amp;nbsp;Use whatever format would enable you to communicate&#xD;
    with the stakeholders so that they can understand the architecture and provide feedback.&amp;nbsp;However, when selecting a&#xD;
    format, it may be helpful to consider the downstream activities that may be able to leverage these materials (for&#xD;
    example, enablement) and choose a format that&amp;nbsp;promotes such reuse.&#xD;
&lt;/p></representationOptions>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ArtifactDescription>
